== Configuration ==

==== OpenRC ====

Add the iwd daemon to the default runlevel and start it up:

{{RootCmd
|rc-update add iwd default
|rc-service iwd start}}

=== Connecting to an access point ===
{{c|Iwctl}} can be used to control iwd. It supports both a commandline interface and an interactive mode. 
A complete commandline would be {{c|iwctl station list}} to see what adapters you might be able to use:

{{Cmd|iwctl station list|output=<pre>
                            Devices in Station Mode
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  Name                State          Scanning
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  wlan0               disconnected
</pre>}}

Interactively, you can use a sequence as follows to connect to a wifi network. First check the status, set it in scanning mode if needed, and then obtain the list of wifi access points. Finally connect to the access point.

{{Cmd|iwctl station wlan0 show|output=<pre>
# station wlan0 show
                                 Station: wlan0
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  Settable  Property            Value
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
            Scanning            no
            State               disconnected

# station wlan0 scan
# station wlan0 get-networks
                               Available networks
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    Network name                    Security  Signal
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    FRITZ!Box 7362 SL               psk       ***
    WLAN-105127                     psk       *

# station wlan0 connect "FRITZ!Box 7362 SL"
Type the network passphrase for FRITZ!Box 7362 SL psk.
Passphrase:
</pre>}}

